```spl
program product
    reads x, y;
    writes out;
    pragma all;
    type
        number = varint(x - 1, y - 1);
        pair = (number, number);
    procedure print (pair: pair);
    begin
        writeln(pair.first);
        writeln(pair.second);
    end;
begin
    for i in 1 ..#x loop
        for j in 1 ..#y loop
            writeln(i // j);
        end loop;
    end loop;
end.
```

This SPL program uses the `varint` function to represent integers, and it uses the `pair` structure to keep track of the two numbers that the program is processing.

